**/.git
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/.vite
**/coverage
**/*.log
.claude/
.github/
devops/
**/.env*
**/*.md
# …but the store catalog ships REAL markdown at runtime — agent definitions
# (agents/*/{charter,instruct}.md), knowledge (*.md), and READMEs. Excluding them
# made the store build a manifest without any of those files, so an installed
# app/integration downloaded only functions + package.json → no handler agent →
# "agent not found" / "no webhook binding". Re-include BOTH catalog trees:
#   store/projects/** — project-apps · store/spaces/** — installable spaces (incl. integration-*)
!store/projects/**/*.md
!store/spaces/**/*.md
# …and the docs site IS markdown: org/ (lmthing.org) bundles every doc into the
# SPA at build time via `import.meta.glob('/docs/**/*.md', ?raw)`. With `**/*.md`
# excluded from the build context the glob resolved to {} and the shipped image
# rendered "Page not found" on every route.
!org/docs/**/*.md
sdk/org/docs/
